%h1 First Executor
%p.section-text You should specify who you wish to administer your estate and carry out your wishes in your will. It s advisable to have more than one executor but less than four. You can have professional executors and Notary Express can act in this capacity.
%hr

= form_for [@will, @executor] do |f|

  = f.fields_for :first_executor_general_detail do |builder|
    = render "general_details/general_details_form", :builder => builder, :nested_origin => @executor.first_executor_general_detail

  .field
    = question "03030"
    = f.check_box :second

  %div{"data-condition" => ":checked", "data-require" => "#executor_second", "data-true" => "hide"}
    = f.submit 'Save', class: "button radius", :onclick => "return confirm('It is strongly advisable to appoint an executor. Are you sure you wish to proceed without appointing an executor')"
  %div{"data-condition" => ":checked", "data-require" => "#executor_second", "data-false" => "hide"}
    = f.submit 'Save', class: "button radius"